A RESOLUTION
1 Commending The Good Samaritan Health Centers of Gwinnett; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, The Good Samaritan Health Centers of Gwinnett (Good Sam Gwinnett) is a
3 non-profit organization dedicated to serving the uninsured and low-income residents of
4 Gwinnett County through two charitable clinics, Good Sam East and Good Sam West, both
5 located in Norcross; and
6 WHEREAS, since its founding in 2005, Good Sam Gwinnett has provided low-cost medical
7 care, dental care, counseling services, and medication assistance across the lifespan of
8 patients in need, serving more than 300,000 individuals over the past 20 years; and
9 WHEREAS, Good Sam Gwinnett operates with the mission of demonstrating Christ's love
10 by ensuring that no individual in the community needlessly suffers from treatable health or
11 dental conditions due to lack of access to care; and
12 WHEREAS, the organization strives to achieve its goals of providing quality, affordable
13 healthcare and dental services to the uninsured, reducing the burden on emergency rooms for
14 non-emergency services, and equipping future medical professionals to address the unique
15 challenges faced by disadvantaged patient populations; and
