16 WHEREAS, by fulfilling its mission, Good Sam Gwinnett helps to eliminate health
17 disparities among the poor and uninsured, reduces the overall cost of indigent care in the
18 healthcare system, and enhances awareness within the medical community of the needs of
19 underserved populations; and
20 WHEREAS, under the leadership of CEO Shameka Allen and with a staff of over 50 full-
21 and part-time front line workers, The Good Samaritan Health Centers of Gwinnett remains
22 committed to providing compassionate and comprehensive healthcare services to those who
23 might otherwise go without.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body commend The Good Samaritan Health Centers of Gwinnett for its
26 unwavering dedication to serving uninsured and low-income individuals and extend best
27 wishes for continued success in its mission.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to The
30 Good Samaritan Health Centers of Gwinnett.
